ğŸ”¹ What is an Ordered List?
An ordered list is used when sequence matters.

HTML tags:
<ol>
   <li>Item</li>
</ol>

ğŸ”¹ Real-life use cases:
1.Step-by-step instructions
2.Rankings
3.Processes (registration steps)

ğŸ”¹ Attributes of <ol> (IMPORTANT) type
Controls numbering style:
1 â†’ Numbers (default)
A â†’ Uppercase letters
a â†’ Lowercase letters
I â†’ Roman numerals
i â†’ Lowercase roman

start:Defines starting number

reversed:Reverses numbering

ğŸ”¹ What is an Unordered List?
Used when order does NOT matter.

HTML tags:
<ul>
   <li>Item</li>
</ul>

ğŸ”¹ Real-life use cases
1. Navigation menus
2. Feature lists
3. Categories

ğŸ”¹ Bullet styles (via CSS usually)
HTML has type attribute (deprecated), but we mention it for understanding:
disc
circle
square

ğŸ‘‰ Styling is done using CSS, not HTML.

ğŸ”¹ What is a Nested List?
